13.body:
The backticks ` ` makes a template string, exactly like a normal string using double quotes " " or single quotes ' ', but you're able to use the dollarsign curlybrace syntax ${...} to insert values. To type ` ` press Shift + the key left of backspace. Example: let a = 5;
let myString = `word ${a} word word ${3 + 5 * a} word word`; throw new Error("error message") consists of a throw keyword/operator and a thrown value, in this case a new object of the Error-class, which is used for this purpose. Throwing a value (most often reffered to as 'throwing an exception/error', or just 'throwing'), means stopping whatever the program is doing, and going into 'exception-mode'. This is called 'exceptions'. Instead of the program crashing, when we throw an exception, we can also try and catch the exception, which is something you can read here . In Javascript and Typescript we use single equals = for assignment, eg: let a = 5;, and we use triple equals 'strict equality operator' === for testing whether 2 values are the same. The 'strict in-equality operator' !== tests whether 2 values are not the same. In Typescript we use === instead of ==, because of annoying history you can read here .

25.body: Lav en mappe, fx my-typescript-project på skrivebordet. Åben VS Code Klik File i venstre hjørne -> Klik Open Folder -> Find og marker mappen du lavede -> Klik Open. Åben 'command pallet' ved at trykke ctrl + shift + p -> søg på deno init, tryk enter på Deno: Initialize Workspace Configuration og tryk enter til de 2 spørgsmål. Klik New File i 'explorer'-fanen, og giv filen navnet main.ts Åben filen ved at dobbeltklikke på den. Skrive koden fra før i filen. Gem filen ved at trykke ctrl + s på dit tastatur. Åben en terminal (hvis ikke den er åben allerede) ved at trykke ctrl + j eller ved at klikke og trække op fra overkanten af bundlinjen i VS Code. Skriv deno run main.ts og tryk enter.

5.body: To test that everything works, write console.log("hello world"); in a file, and save it as main.ts. Now run the file by typing deno run main.ts in a terminal/command line.
5.breadcrumbs: Calculator in Typescript » Print hello world
5.title: Print hello world

6.body: Create a folder, eg. my-typescript-project on the desktop. Open VS Code Click File up in the left corner -> Click Open Folder -> Find and mark the folder you created -> Click Open. Open command pallet by pressing ctrl + shift + p -> search for deno init, press enter on Deno: Initialize Workspace Configuration and press enter for the 2 questions. Click New File in the explorer tab, and name it main.ts Open it by double clicking it. Write the code above. Save by hitting ctrl + s on your keyboard. Open a terminal (if not already open) by hitting ctrl + j or dragging up from the top of the bottombar in VS Code. Type deno run main.ts and press enter.
